$ git config --global user.name "John Doe"
$ git config --global user.email "johndoe@example.com"

View list og git users
- git config --list


Initialising Git in a project
- git init projectname

Add when youâ€™re ready to save a copy of the current state of the project, you stage changes with git add
- git add filename or git add *.c

Commit
- git commit -m "commit message"

Cloning a Repository
- git clone url to repository 

View git log
- git log 

Exiting git log
- To stop viewing git log output, press q (which stands for quit).

Getting Colored Output
- To get colored diff output, run git config --global color.ui auto

The command Caroline types to checkout the "Revert controls" commit is 
- git checkout b0678b161fcf74467ed3a63110557e3d6229cfa6.


The view project branch and current branch
- git branch

To create branch of a project
- git branch 'name of branch you wish to create'

To switch to new branch
- git checkout 'name of new branch'

To create new branchto retain commits
- git checkout -b 'new branch name'

To merger to branches 
- git merge 'first branch name'  'second branch name'

To delete a branch
- git branch -d 'name of branch'








